The paper deals with deep neural networks and their tradeoff between computational effort and accuracy, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of confidence levels derived from softmax outputs is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also discusses experimentation with architectures based on ResNet, which is a popular convolutional neural network architecture commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL).
